This is a python script to download coursera lecture videos and files.

Requirements:
	python 2.6
	mechanize 0.2.5
	beautifulsoup 4

First edit the config.py file:
	username
	password
	files to download: mp4, srt, txt, pdf, pptx

To start the download, execute in a terminal:
	python get.py <coursename>
Coursename can be determined from the url of the course.

eg: https://class.coursera.org/*nlp*/lecture/index
To download lectures of nlp class, execute:
	`python get.py nlp`

Limitations:
	* Initially it will download all the lectures from the beginning. To download selected lectures, hack the get.py script
	* It does not resume incomplete downloads.
